<subSubSection pageId="61" pageNumber="545" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="61.[2014,2609,745,1172]" pageId="61" pageNumber="545">
Taxonomic definition of S. 
<taxonomicName box="[2449,2609,824,857]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Sturnira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="545" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oporaphilum">oporaphilum</taxonomicName>
has been obscured by its use as a senior synonym of S. 
<taxonomicName box="[2225,2326,903,936]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Sturnira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="545" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ludovici">ludovici</taxonomicName>
or as a junior synonym of S. 
<taxonomicName box="[2153,2229,942,975]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Sturnira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="545" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lilium">Lilium</taxonomicName>
, orjust confused with S. 
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Sturnira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="545" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bogotensis">bogotensis</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
